racism.

36:38.229 --> 36:39.998 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Reverend Billings, thank you for
joining us.

36:40.098 --> 36:41.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. DAVID BILLINGS, People's
Institute for
Survival and Beyond: Well, it's
my honor.

36:42.067 --> 36:44.903 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Your
organization
is over 30 years old, and it was
founded to

36:45.003 --> 36:49.541 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
combat racism, among other
things. How do
you define racism?

36:49.641 --> 36:54.846 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
REV. DAVID BILLINGS: We define
it as race
prejudice, plus power.

36:54.946 --> 36:59.751 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Individual racism, like how we
feel about
each other and what we might
call each other,

36:59.851 --> 37:05.523 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
is just a byproduct of an
arrangement that
goes all the way back before the
nation's

37:05.623 --> 37:06.524 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
founding.

37:06.624 --> 37:08.393 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: What do
you mean?

37:08.493 --> 37:12.564 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. DAVID BILLINGS: One of the
founders'
greatest fears was that poor
Europeans who'd

37:12.664 --> 37:17.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
come over here as indentured,
there was a
great a fear that they would
join up with

37:18.002 --> 37:25.510 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Africans who were being
enslaved and indigenous
people and overthrow before they
even got

37:25.610 --> 37:27.312 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
started.

37:27.412 --> 37:32.784 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, it would be the creation of
race that
will compromise poor and what we
today we'd

37:32.884 --> 37:41.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
call working-class whites. And
it makes us
hesitant, has always made us
hesitant to organize

37:41.860 --> 37:44.896 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
with people of color, especially
black people.

37:44.996 --> 37:51.903 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This country constantly and
still does treats
racism as it were just a matter
of personal

37:52.003 --> 37:57.876 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
relationships. And it's not, you
know? That's
why so many of us who are white
can say, well,

37:57.976 --> 38:02.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm not racist, you know, I have
got friends
who are black, all the sort of
things.

38:02.680 --> 38:07.085 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: But
there were Civil
Rights Act, Voting Rights Act.
Didn't that

38:07.185 --> 38:08.987 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
change things a little bit?

38:09.087 --> 38:11.789 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. DAVID BILLINGS: Oh, it
changed -- you
know, they had great impact, the
Voting Rights

38:11.890 --> 38:15.593 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Act and everything, but we have
to -- we are
fighting today to preserve it.

38:15.693 --> 38:25.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At the People's Institute, I
will speak to
people that are white like me.
There's a bitterness,

38:25.970 --> 38:29.040 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
there's an anger about equal
rights, you know?

38:29.140 --> 38:30.875 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: You
experience that?
People tell you that?

38:30.975 --> 38:34.212 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
REV. DAVID BILLINGS: Oh, yes.
Oh, yes.

38:34.312 --> 38:40.485 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
When we first started, no
systems were asking
us to work with them. None of
the great systems

38:40.585 --> 38:47.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
like universities or hospitals
or health care
would even admit that racism was
an issue

38:47.192 --> 38:48.693 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
for them.

38:48.793 --> 38:50.828 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Tell me
what you and
your organization are doing.

38:50.929 --> 38:58.670 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. DAVID BILLINGS: We get
invited now to
be a part of symposiums, to be a
part of long-term

38:58.770 --> 39:07.011 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
organizing effort within --
given large systems
to work with them for a period
of months,

39:07.111 --> 39:15.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
even years, to analyze how race
and racism
is impacting their outcomes,
their work.

39:16.087 --> 39:25.129 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's taking off all around
the country.
We start off, usually, with a
small group

39:25.230 --> 39:32.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of people within a larger system
who say,
we want to go through one of the
undoing racism

39:32.737 --> 39:41.512 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
workshops, because the purpose
of the undoing
racism workshop is to eventually
be the foundation

39:41.613 --> 39:50.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for a longer organizing effort
within the
institution, understanding
racism, its history,

39:50.188 --> 39:58.896 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you know, its impact today, and
how the nation
is as it changes, how the racism
begins to

39:58.997 --> 40:06.170 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
resist the structural racism,
begins to resist
societal change.

40:06.271 --> 40:15.079 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We do an ongoing community
organizing/undoing
racism workshop, because it
takes us a year

40:15.179 --> 40:22.120 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or two to cover, say, hundreds
of people in
the schools of social work of
New York City,

40:22.220 --> 40:23.855 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and we work with every one of
them.

40:23.955 --> 40:26.491 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: And you
find that
these people don't know about
race?

40:26.591 --> 40:27.525 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
REV. DAVID BILLINGS: Yes.

40:27.625 --> 40:29.394 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: And what
do you find?

40:29.494 --> 40:35.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. DAVID BILLINGS: What we
find is that
people understand race, but they
don't understand

40:35.133 --> 40:37.101 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
organizing.

40:37.201 --> 40:42.040 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You can't teach racism away. A
lot of us think
you can. You can't legislate it
away, as important

40:42.140 --> 40:47.912 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as the Voting Rights Act and
things like that
are. There's not one institution
in this country

40:48.012 --> 40:55.119 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
where they can say: There's no
racism here.
We have solved it.

40:55.219 --> 41:02.927 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I come out of the church. You
would think
the church would be in the lead
around tackling

41:03.027 --> 41:04.796 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
racism.

41:04.896 --> 41:07.231 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Are
white churches
doing what they should be doing?
I know we're

41:07.332 --> 41:09.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
generalizing, but in general?

41:09.200 --> 41:13.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. DAVID BILLINGS: Very few.
Very few, maybe
less than there were a
generation ago.

41:13.504 --> 41:19.077 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: I think
just about
everybody agrees there's a very
toxic atmosphere

41:19.177 --> 41:23.881 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
